Analysis of the Main Target Image
--------------------------------
•  Overall there are two separate “builds” in the scene.

(1) Left‐Hand Structure (6 blocks total, effectively three “layers”):
   – Bottom Layer:
     ◦ One orange triangular/wedge block at the left/rear corner  
     ◦ One green rectangular prism (horizontal) forming the main base  
   – Middle Layer:
     ◦ A blue cube stacked on top of the green rectangle  
     ◦ A yellow cube stacked on top of (or adjacent to) the blue cube  
   – Vertical Column and Top:
     ◦ An orange cylinder standing upright behind those cubes  
     ◦ A red “U‐shaped” cradle block resting on top of the cylinder  

(2) Right‐Hand Structure (7 blocks total, three layers):
   – Bottom Layer:
     ◦ A red arch block in the center  
     ◦ One orange wedge on each side of the arch (left and right)  
   – Middle Layer:
     ◦ A green cube on the left half  
     ◦ A blue cube on the right half  
   – Top (Roof) Layer:
     ◦ Two orange triangular wedges meeting in the middle like a gable roof  

Selection of Required Blocks (by Dictionary Index)
-------------------------------------------------
Below are the block‐dictionary indices that match exactly (same shape, color, and orientation) as seen in the target:

• Left‐Hand Structure  
  1) Orange wedge: index 14 (used once)  
  2) Green horizontal rectangular block: index 8  
  3) Blue cube: index 4  
  4) Yellow cube: index 7  
  5) Orange cylinder (vertical): index 11  
  6) Red U‐shaped cradle (concave on top): index 2  

• Right‐Hand Structure  
  1) Red arch block (arch on bottom): index 1  
  2) Orange wedge (bottom left): index 14 (reused)  
  3) Orange wedge (bottom right): index 16  
  4) Green cube: index 5  
  5) Blue cube: index 4 (reused)  
  6) Orange wedge (roof left): index 14 (reused again)  
  7) Orange wedge (roof right): index 16 (reused again)  

Step‐by‐Step Assembly Instructions
---------------------------------
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 14  
  Step2: Move block with index 8  
  Step3: Move block with index 4  
  Step4: Move block with index 7  
  Step5: Move block with index 11  
  Step6: Move block with index 2  
  Step7: Move block with index 1  
  Step8: Move block with index 14  
  Step9: Move block with index 16  
  Step10: Move block with index 5  
  Step11: Move block with index 4  
  Step12: Move block with index 14  
  Step13: Move block with index 16  
}
